<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-11-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="185" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Young</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,<lb/>Guatemala and
                                        Honduras</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-11-02"><hi rend="italic">Nov. 2, 1893</hi></date>.
                                (Received Nov. 16.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 33.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that
                            reports coming from all sections of this Republic confirm me in the
                            belief that the new order of things has been accepted with satisfaction
                            by all the people of the Republic.</p>
                        <pb facs="0262" n="154" xml:id="pg_154"/>
                        <p>The President has inaugurated many new and wholesome measures calculated
                            to lighten the burdens of the people, and he is rapidly winning their
                            esteem and affection.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">P. M. B. Young.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>